Assignment: Employee Management System for a Consulting Firm
Scenario:
You are building a module for an HR system at a consulting firm. The firm has different types of employees, primarily FullTimeEmployee and Contractor. Each type has a different way of calculating their salary and benefits.

Coding Requirements:

1. Abstract Class: Employee

Attributes (all private):

employeeId: String

name: String

email: String

Constructor: Parameterized constructor to initialize all fields. Validate that: employeeId and name are not null or empty, and email contains the '@' symbol.

Methods:

public abstract double calculateSalary();

public abstract String getBenefits();

Getters for all fields.

toString() method to print basic employee details.

2. Concrete Class: FullTimeEmployee (extends Employee)

Additional Attribute (private):

monthlySalary: double

Constructor: Parameterized constructor to initialize all fields (including parent's). Validate monthlySalary is positive.

Methods (Override):

calculateSalary(): Returns the monthlySalary.

getBenefits(): Returns a String description: "Health Insurance, Paid Leave, Retirement Plan".

3. Concrete Class: Contractor (extends Employee)

Additional Attributes (private):

hourlyRate: double

hoursWorked: int

Constructor: Parameterized constructor to initialize all fields. Validate hourlyRate is positive and hoursWorked is non-negative.

Methods (Override):

calculateSalary(): Returns the product of hourlyRate and hoursWorked.

getBenefits(): Returns a String: "No standard benefits".

4. Execution Class: HRSystem

In the main method, display a menu:

text
Select Employee Type:
1. Full-Time Employee
2. Contractor
Use a Scanner and switch statement to capture the user's choice.

Based on the choice, prompt the user for all necessary details to create either a FullTimeEmployee or a Contractor object.

After creating the object, display the employee's details, their calculated salary, and their benefits.

Test Cases for Output & Input Validation
Test Case 1: Happy Path - Full-Time Employee

text
Select Employee Type:
1. Full-Time Employee
2. Contractor
1
Enter Employee ID: FTE101
Enter Name: Alice Smith
Enter Email: alice.smith@firm.com
Enter Monthly Salary: 75000
--- Employee Details ---
ID: FTE101, Name: Alice Smith, Email: alice.smith@firm.com
Type: Full-Time
Calculated Salary: $75000.0
Benefits: Health Insurance, Paid Leave, Retirement Plan
Test Case 2: Happy Path - Contractor

text
Select Employee Type:
1. Full-Time Employee
2. Contractor
2
Enter Employee ID: CONT202
Enter Name: Bob Johnson
Enter Email: bob.j@firm.com
Enter Hourly Rate: 45.50
Enter Hours Worked: 80
--- Employee Details ---
ID: CONT202, Name: Bob Johnson, Email: bob.j@firm.com
Type: Contractor
